Description: ENA (Shaffer, D. W. (2017) Quantitative Ethnography. ISBN:
        0578191687) is a method used to identify meaningful and
        quantifiable patterns in discourse or reasoning. ENA moves
        beyond the traditional frequency-based assessments by examining
        the structure of the co-occurrence, or connections in coded
        data. Moreover, compared to other methodological approaches,
        ENA has the novelty of (1) modeling whole networks of
        connections and (2) affording both quantitative and qualitative
        comparisons between different network models.  Shaffer, D.W.,
        Collier, W., & Ruis, A.R. (2016).
